HEADWORD: Hyperpyrexia
<hw>Hy`per*py*rex"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Hyper-</er>, and <er>Pyrexia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
condition of excessive fever; an elevation of temperature in a disease,
in excess of the limit usually observed in that disease.</def>⟦br⟧
